<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode.SetPolygonWindingOrder" Title="SetPolygonWindingOrder method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode">IStateGroupNode</PageRef> ->
    SetPolygonWindingOrder
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>SetPolygonWindingOrder</TypeRef> method sets the <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode.PolygonWindingOrder">PolygonWindingOrder</PageRef> for the <TypeRef>IStateGroupNode</TypeRef>. All child renderable will use the set winding order to determine their facing direction. It is <TypeRef>PolygonWindingOrder::CounterClockwise</TypeRef> by default.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[void SetPolygonWindingOrder(PolygonWindingOrder windingOrder);]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="PolygonWindingOrder!cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode.PolygonWindingOrder" Name="windingOrder">
          The polygon winding order to use
        </ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
